                            <comment id="13754119" author="enis" created="Thu, 29 Aug 2013 22:10:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch which changes hbase.rootdir to not have the &lt;a href=&quot;file://&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;file://&lt;/a&gt; prefix. Since &lt;a href=&quot;file:///&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;file:///&lt;/a&gt; is the defaultFS, it should not make any difference whether we have it or not. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tested the patch on linux and windows by starting hbase locally. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
